main event: A white or yellow-white/silver object was observed in the sky over Jefferson, Ohio on May 20, 1966 for about 30 minutes.
interesting points: The object appeared to be brighter than the brightest stars.
The object was observed to be stationary at times and then suddenly speed up.
The object did not appear to leave any trail or smoke.
The witness estimated the object to be about 60 feet away.
Multiple witnesses in the area reported seeing similar objects.
sighted object: A white or yellow-white/silver, star-like object
